      "description": "Make <html lang> attribute dynamic. Since layout.tsx is a server component, the simplest compliant approach is to add a client wrapper or use a cookie-based locale detection. Minimum viable fix: move lang to a client component that reads from encrypted localStorage via the i18n context.",
      "note": "This requires architectural decision: either (a) use Next.js i18n routing with locale in URL, or (b) use a suppressHydrationWarning client component that updates the lang attribute post-mount via useEffect. Option (b) is least invasive.",
      "changes": [
        {
          "action": "create_client_component",
          "file": "components/layout/HtmlLang.tsx",
          "code": "\"use client\";\nimport { useEffect } from 'react';\nimport { useTranslation } from '@/lib/i18n';\nexport function HtmlLang() {\n  const { language } = useTranslation();\n  useEffect(() => {\n    document.documentElement.lang = language;\n  }, [language]);\n  return null;\n}"
        },
        {
          "action": "add_to_layout_body",
          "description": "Add <HtmlLang /> inside <I18nProvider> in app/layout.tsx"
        }
